8	9	alaiat_ahmed_5067884 (1).pdf	\N	Ahmed Alaiat\n(505) 210-2025 ahmed@albousaifilaw.com Cleveland, OH 44133linkedin.com/in/ahmed-alaiat-albousaifi\nEDUCATION\nDoctorate Degree: Doctor of Juridical Science (SJD) Cleveland, OH\nCase Western Reserve University School of Law Jan 2024\n● Thesis: Assessing the Adequacy of Force Majeure Clauses in International Petroleum Agreements: Legal Chal-\nlenges and Implications for Contracting Parties in the Face of Modern Geopolitical Realities- Libyan Focus\nMaster of Laws (LL.M) in International Business Law Cleveland, OH\nCase Western Reserve University School of Law May 2018\n● Certificate of Concentration: Public International Law\nBachelor of Laws (LL.B) Tripoli, Libya\nUniversity of Tripoli Faculty of Law\n• Diploma of laws: Law Diploma in Commercial and Civil Law Studies\nWORK EXPERIENCE\nTarabot Law Firm Tripoli, Libya\nAssociate Attorney, Part-Time Fall 2023– Present\n Drafting and Reviewing Legal Documents: Drafting, reviewing, and amending legal documents, including con-\ntracts and memos, for accuracy and legal compliance.\n Performing Legal Research and Analysis: Performing legal research and analysis on international law, com-\nmercial law, and arbitration to provide up-to-date advice.\n Ensuring Compliance and Risk Management: Ensuring compliance with legal standards and regulations; iden-\ntifying and mitigating legal risks.\n Managing Cross-border Legal Issues: Managing cross-border legal issues by understanding different legal sys-\ntems for smooth international transactions.\n Leading Project Management: Leading legal projects from start to finish, ensuring timely progress and adapting\nto changes.\nCase Western Reserve University School of Law Cleveland, OH\nCWRU Law Library Assistant, Research Assistant Fall 2019, Spring 2020, Fall 2022\n Organizing and Cataloging Resources: Actively organizing and cataloging legal resources and books to en-\nhance the accessibility of library materials for students and faculty.\n Assisting with Legal Research: Assisting students and faculty with legal research by providing guidance on uti-\nlizing databases and legal research tools effectively.\n Maintaining Digital Resources: Updating and maintaining digital resources and databases, ensuring they are\ncurrent and accessible to users.\nOffice of Global Studies Coordinator Fall 2019 and Fall 2022\n Coordinating International Programs: Coordinating international study programs and exchanges, ensuring a\nsmooth and enriching experience for students, and visiting scholars.\n Developing Outreach Materials: Creating and updating outreach materials, including brochures and websites, to\npromote global study opportunities.\n Facilitating Cross-cultural Communication: Facilitating cross-cultural communication and support for interna-\ntional students and scholars, enhancing their integration and engagement with the campus community.\nAdministrative Office Coordinator Fall 2018\n Streamlining Administrative Processes: Streamlining administrative processes and systems to improve effi-\nciency and service delivery within the office.\n\n Coordinating Meetings and Events: Coordinating logistics for meetings and events, including scheduling, venue\narrangements, and technology setup.\n Supporting Office Communication: Managing internal communication systems, ensuring timely and accurate\ndissemination of information to staff and faculty.\nUniversity of Arizona, School of Middle Eastern & North African Studies Tucson, AZ\nLanguage Partner Spring - Summer 2016\n Facilitating Language Acquisition: Actively facilitating the acquisition of Arabic language skills through im-\nmersive conversation practices and interactive language exercises.\n Enhancing Cultural Understanding: Enhancing students' understanding of Arabic culture through structured\ncultural workshops and informal discussions, bridging cultural gaps and fostering global awareness.\n Developing Educational Materials: Creating and updating educational materials and resources, including lesson\nplans and language practice exercises, tailored to meet the diverse needs of students.\n Analyzing Immigration Trends: Analyzing current trends in immigration and their effects on the U.S. economy\nand innovation, contributing to academic discussions and insights.\n Presenting Research Findings: Presenting research findings on the impact of immigration on the U.S. economy\nand innovation through seminars and academic papers, engaging with the academic community.\nSKILLS\nTechnology-Based:\n Proficient in Microsoft Office, Tableau, JMP, and various operating systems (Windows, Unix, MacOS)\n Familiarities with legal databases and software to improve research, document management, and remote commu-\nnication.\n Experienced in maintaining software and hardware systems Proficient in utilizing technology to enhance produc-\ntivity and streamline processes within legal practice.\n Experienced in project management tools, effectively organizing tasks and tracking progress to ensure timely\ncompletion of assignments.\n Expertise in data visualization to analyze complex legal information and present findings clearly and concisely.\n Committed to continuous learning, staying updated on the latest technological advancements to leverage innova-\ntive solutions meeting evolving client needs.\nBusiness & Law:\n Problem-solving abilities, utilizing analytical research, creativity, and logical thinking.\n Flexible and resourceful team player who excels in fast-paced environments, effectively solving problems.\n Effectively communicated with students through various channels to provide necessary help and support.\n Pursuing ongoing learning in international commercial law and arbitration through seminars and workshops.\n Collaborating with attorneys and teams to develop strategies and solutions, sharing knowledge and best practices.\n Versatile and driven legal professional adept at seamlessly acclima