enarios and develop\nproblem-solving skills essential for success in the legal field.\nI would welcome the opportunity to discuss how my experience and teaching approach could contribute\nto your law program. Thank you for your consideration, and I look forward to the possibility of joining\nyour esteemed faculty.\nSincerely,\nJason I. Bess\n570-417-9688\nJason.Bess@gmail.com\n\nJason I. Bess\n(570) 417.9688 | Jason.Bess@gmail.com\nLEGAL EXPERIENCE\nSELLMARK CORPORATION\nVice President, General Counsel Mansfield, TX January, 2024 – current\n• Legal Strategy and Advisory\no Develop and implement global and company-wide legal strategy aligned with business goals.\no Provide comprehensive legal advice to executives and senior management on contracts,\ncompliance, and risk management.\no Act as liaison between the company and external stakeholders, including regulators and industry\ngroups.\n• Contract and Intellectual Property Management\no Draft and negotiate contracts with clients, vendors, and partners.\no Oversee management company’s intellectual property portfolio, including patents, trademarks,\ncopyrights, and trade secrets.\no Develop and execute IP strategy, including protection, enforcement, and licensing/monetization\nof IP assets.\n• Compliance and Risk Management\no Ensure company compliance with relevant laws and regulations in US, LATAM, EU and\nThailand, including data protection and industry-specific regulations.\no Monitor legislative changes and adjust company policies and practices accordingly.\no Identify potential legal risks and develop mitigation strategies.\n▪ Develop and implement internal policies and procedures for legal compliance and risk\nmanagement.\n• Corporate Governance and Policy Development\no Maintain corporate governance practices in line with legal requirements and best practices.\no Support board of directors and management with governance issues and documentation.\no Provide company-wide training and resources on legal matters and company policies.\n• Litigation and Dispute Resolution\no Oversee legal disputes and litigation involving the company.\no Coordinate with external legal counsel and manage the company’s legal budget.\no Handle dispute resolution, including managing outside counsel when necessary.\n• Mergers and Acquisitions\no Support legal aspects of mergers, acquisitions, and other corporate transactions.\no Conduct due diligence and address legal aspects of transactions.\n• Team and Resource Management\no Lead and manage the legal department, including recruiting, mentoring, and evaluating team\nmembers.\no Allocate resources and manage the legal budget effectively.\nAUTOZONE, INC.\nDirector, Corporate Legal Memphis, TN June 2017 – January 2024\n• Business Transactions and Commercial Contracts\no Manage and provide legal advice on strategic business transactions globally.\no Lead the contracts management lifecycle.\no Serve as primary attorney to review, draft, and negotiate contracts for a variety of business unit\nsuch as, Commercial, IT (including software and technology licensing, SaaS, PaaS, cloud hosting,\ncustom development, supply side licensing, etc.), Treasury, Finance, Human Resources, and\nmore.\n\no Primary attorney for ALLDATA LLC, a global SaaS subsidiary of AutoZone.\no Manage a team of global attorneys and paralegals responsible for AutoZone’s domestic and\nforeign subsidiaries in Europe, the Americas, and Brazil.\n• Corporate Governance; Compliance\no Develop and maintain subject matter expertise in areas of data use/protection laws and advise on\nhow they impact AutoZone’s business.\n▪ Created DPAs for AutoZone and subsidiaries while advising and implementing\norganizational changes for various privacy regulations including GDPR, CCPA/CPRA,\nHIPAA, FTC regulations and more.\no Advise executive team and business partners on wide variety of corporate legal matters, conflict\nresolution, and IP protection.\no Responsible for AutoZone aircraft operation contracts and policy including SMS and FOM\no Lead compliance projects as they arise while working with cross functional departments and\noutside resources.\no Provide training and advise on Privacy, Antitrust, and FCPA matters.\no Serve on AutoZone Benefits Committee and CERT/CSIRT Committee\no Implement procedural changes throughout the enterprise to improve efficiency within the contract\nprocess.\no Manage all aspects of annual meetings, including preparing agendas, scripts, presentations and\nminutes for foreign subsidiaries.\n• Securities Law\no Prepare, review and file formal SEC disclosures for Section 16 reports (Forms 3, 4 and 5)\no Assist in preparation of periodic and current reports (Forms 10-K, 10-Q and 8-K), annual proxy\nstatements, and more.\no Assist or lead commercial paper or bond offerings.\n• Assist in other areas of corporate law (executive compensation, M&A, financing transactions) as needed.\n• Manage team of attorneys and paralegals.\nTOYOTA FINANCIAL SERVICES Plano, TX September 2015 – June 2017\nManaging Attorney\n• Responsible for a team of 4 contract managers and 1 business analyst\no Reduced average contract cycle time from three months to 18 days.\n• Drafted, reviewed, and negotiated various commercial contracts in support of multiple business units and\ninternal departments.\n• Provided counsel to internal business departments on applicable rules, regulations, and alternative business\nsolutions.\n• Served as an escalation point for contract negotiations and management activities.\n• Interpreted legal, contractual, and regulatory requirements to facilitate contract negotiations.\n• Assisted in the development and implementation of new corporate policies\nNOVATION Irving, TX November 2014 – May 2015\nLegal Counsel (Contract)\n• Drafted, negotiated, and provided advice and counseling on healthcare supply and distribution contracts.\n• Conducted legal issues training classes for Novation employees.\n• Performed general corporate counsel functions such as researching and advising client departments on\nregulatory and legal issues.\nCORELOGIC Westlake, TX November 2013 – November 2014\n\nSSC Legal Manager\n• Managed a team of 7 Contract Administrators and Managers.\n• Drafted and negotiated commercial and vendor agreements with third parties.\n• Advised internal partners, staff, and business units on contract terms and liability protections.\n• Conducted due diligence for transactions and managed risk.\n• Organized and maintained all contracts and related documents.\nPUBLICATIONS/ SPEAKING ENGAGEMENTS\n“How to develop your in-house team”\nhttps://www.inhouseblog.com/how-to-develop-your-in-house-team/\n“Agile or Waterfall: Balancing Legal and IT needs with Acceptance Criteria”\nhttps://www.lawinsider.com/resources/drafting/agile-or-waterfall-balancing-legal-and-it-needs-with-acceptance-criteria\n“Operationalizing Privacy Law in the Transactional Realm”\nPrivacy + Security’s Fall Forum on November 10, 2023; Washington D.C.\n“GenAI use cases for in-house counsel”\nThomson Reuters & In-House Connect on July 17, 2024\nEDUCATION\nTEXAS A&M UNIVERSITY LAW SCHOOL Fort Worth, TX 2013\nJuris Doctorate\nTexas Bar License 24081673\nKING’S COLLEGE, Wilkes-Barre, PA 2010\nMCGOWAN SCHOOL OF BUSINESS\nBachelors of Science in Business Administration\nGeneral counsel associate assistant general counsel SaaS IT Information Technology lead contract review negotiation manage manager privacy\n\nJason Bess\nPersonal Statement\nAs an experienced in-house counsel with over a decade of practice in diverse business\nenvironments, I am excited to transition into academia and share my knowledge with aspiring\nlegal professionals. My teaching philosophy and approach are shaped by my extensive practical\nexperience, managerial experience with new attorneys, and a deep commitment to nurturing\nthe next generation of lawyers.\nMy teaching philosophy is built on four key pillars:\n1. Fostering Critical Thinking: I believe that the cornerstone of legal education is developing\nstudents' ability to analyze complex situations, identify key issues, and formulate reasoned\narguments. Through case studies, debates, and problem-solving exercises, I will challenge\nstudents to think critically and approach legal problems from multiple angles.\n2. Promoting Ethical Decision-Making: In today's complex business world, ethical considerations\nare paramount. I will emphasize the importance of integrity and ethical conduct, encouraging\nstudents to consider the moral implications of legal decisions and to develop a strong ethical\ncompass that will guide them throughout their careers.\n3. Developing Pragmatic Problem-Solving Skills: Drawing from my experience in both Fortune\n300 companies and small businesses, I will focus on teaching students how to develop practical,\nimplementable solutions to real-world legal challenges. This includes honing skills in\nnegotiation, drafting, and strategic thinking.\n4. Preparing for Multifaceted Challenges: The legal landscape is ever-evolving, and lawyers must\nbe adaptable. I will strive to equip students with a diverse skill set that prepares them for the\nvaried challenges they will face in their legal careers, from interpreting new regulations to\nnavigating complex corporate structures.\nTo bring this philosophy to life, I plan to:\n1. Incorporate Real-World Case Studies: I will draw upon my extensive professional experience\nto provide students with authentic, complex scenarios that mirror the challenges they will face\nin their careers.\n\n2. Implement Interactive Learning Methods: My classes will feature negotiation simulations, real\nworld ethical dilemmas, and group projects to encourage active participation and collaborative\nlearning.\n3. Invite Guest Speakers: I will leverage my professional network to bring in practicing attorneys\nand business leaders, offering students diverse perspectives and networking opportunities.\n4. Emphasize Practical Skills: Alongside theoretical knowledge, I will focus on developing\npractical skills such as contract drafting, internal and external client communication, and legal\nresearch techniques.\n5. Integrate Technology: Recognizing the increasing role of technology in legal practice, I will\nincorporate relevant legal tech tools and discussions about their impact on the profession.\n6. Provide Individualized Mentoring: I am committed to being accessible to students, offering\nguidance not just on coursework but also on career paths and professional development.\nBy creating an engaging and interactive learning environment, I aim to inspire students to apply\ntextbook scenarios and develop the critical problem-solving skills essential for success in the\nlegal field. My goal is to not just teach the law, but to cultivate lawyers who are ethical,\npragmatic, and well-prepared for the dynamic challenges of modern legal practice.\nJason I Bess\n570-417-9688\nJason.Bess@gmail.com\n\nJason Bess Contact References\nMaria Leggett\nVice President Assistant General Counsel\nAutoZone, Inc.\n305-570-8366\nAbul Guice\nSenior Corporate Counsel\nVizient, Inc.\n321-704-4258\nPaul Scuibba\nCorporate Litigation Director\nAutoZone, Inc.\n240-338-0361\n\nApplication Forms\nFoster Child Form\nFoster Child\nI was not a foster child\n\nVeteran Status/Identification Form\nVoluntary Self-Identification of Veteran Status\nI do not identify as a veteran\nSurviving Spouse of a Veteran\nI am not a surviving spouse of a veteran\nOrphan of a Veteran\nI am not an orphan of a veteran\n\nClery Act\nAcknowledgement:\nI acknowledge that I have received the above information regarding the Clery Act\n\nNotice of Non-Discrimination\nAcknowledgement:\nI acknowledge that I have received the information above regarding notice of non-discrimination and abuse\n\n	2025-10-10 22:37:15.706775+00	[-0.028140696,0.014407134,-0.032180846,-0.04756061,-0.025499007,0.019700084,-0.008271397,0.0712893,0.047636695,0.06488186,-0.03152254,0.035