n jurisdictions.\n● Drafted and amended merger and acquisition agreements between Fortune 500 companies.\nLANGUAGE, GENERAL SKILLS\n● Bilingual in Spanish and English, Basic French\n● Proficient Microsoft SQL Server, Microsoft PowerBI\n● Advanced Microsoft Excel, Powerpoint Visualizations\n● state insurance laws, contracts and/or tax law Excellent oral and written communication skills,ability to handle multiple projects and assignments effectivelyDraft wills, trusts, and related estate planning documents, Work with partnerships, corporations, and closely-held businesses for estate planning, Conduct research and present complex legal solutions in clear tes\t\n●\nstate insurance laws, contracts and/or tax law Excellent oral and written communication skills,ability to handle multiple projects and assignments effectivelyDraft wills, trusts, and related estate planning documents, Work with partnerships, corporations, and closely-held businesses for estate planning, Conduct research and present complex legal solutions in clear terms\n-- 1 of 6 --\n\nConrado Asenjo Molina, Esq.\n(787) 565-7819 | conrado.asenjo@gmail.com\nDear Hiring Manager:\nMy name is Conrado Asenjo, and I am a licensed attorney, International Tax Advisory Manager\nat Fernway Solutions, LLC. I am applying for the role of lecturer at the University of North Carolina-\nCharlotte’s Belk College of Business. I have worked at Fernway in their inbound and outbound\ntransaction advisory group, with a focus on emerging markets. Some of the transactions include foreign\nsubsidiary establishment, US acquisition of foreign entities, and complex entity restructuring. Before\nFernway, I was at KPMG, LLP in their International Tax group for over two years, where I was part of\ndiverse multinational transactions such as private equity acquisitions, tax reform analysis, including Pillar\n2, as well as compliance requirements for IRS returns. I have gained extensive experience working on\nplanning and consulting projects