mployees). While some sessions were taught in-\nperson, many of these classes were conducted virtually/online, so I am very comfortable\neducating and engaging student-participants online.\nMy educational journey also allows me to bring diverse perspectives and unique viewpoints to an\nEmployment Law, HR Law, or Compliance class/curriculum. I received my bachelor’s degree in\nbusiness administration/marketing, a Master of Arts in Corporate Communications and\nTechnology, and my doctoral degree in Law (Juris Doctor). The Legal and HR leadership roles I\nhave had – combined with these educational experiences – provide me with relevant, real-world\nscenarios/outcomes, bringing concepts to life for students through the power of story.\nA deep-rooted passion for teaching and HR/Labor & Employment law as well as the desire to\nreturn to the calling of “professor,” leads me to seek this extraordinary opportunity with Texas\nA&M. My expertise is best suited to develop/teach courses in the Human Resources and\nEmployment Law, Policy, and Management specialty, or Compliance-related courses.\nI would welcome the opportunity to discuss in more detail how I could add value to the Distance\nEducation curriculum at Texas A&M University, School of Law.\nBest Regards,\nDarren S. Chiappetta\n-- 1 of 22 --\n\nDARREN S. CHIAPPETTA | RESUME \t1\nDarren S. Chiappetta\nEMPLOYMENT ATTORNEY | GLOBAL ER & HR COMPLIANCE EXECUTIVE\nL OS ANGE L E S , CA • 4 0 7 . 4 2 1 . 4 8 5 8 • DS CHI APP E T T A@GMAI L . COM • L I NKE DI N PROF I L E\nWORK\nEXPERIENCE\nMAR 2024 –\nJUN 2024\n(FRACTIONAL) Head of Human Resources & Facility Mgmt./Hospitality\nFIFA World Cup 2026 | Miami, FL - Los Angeles CA (Hybrid)\n• \tFractional Head of HR, building program until local Miami hire is identified.\n• \tCreate and lead all HR efforts for the FIFA World Cup 2026, hosting 48 teams\nand 1,200+ players across 3 countries and 16 venues.\n• \tResponsible for leading all HR operations, including staffing, training, cu