ilosophy. Please do not hesitate to contact me if you have any questions\nor wish to further discuss my candidacy. Thank you for your time and consideration.\nSincerely,\n/s/ Adam G. Gutbezahl\nAdam G. Gutbezahl\n-- 1 of 9 --\n\nADAM G. GUTBEZAHL\n48 Rice Spring Lane | Wayland, MA 01778 | 508.649.4216 | adam.gutbezahl@gmail.com\nE X P E R I E N C E\nLitigation Attorney\nRuberto, Israel & Weiner, P.C. | Boston, MA Nov. 2020 - Present\n• Served as first chair for trials in Massachusetts Superior Court and Land Court and obtained favorable\njudgments for clients.\n• Research, prepare, and successfully argue numerous motions, including motions to dismiss, motions for\njudgment on the pleadings, and motions for summary judgment.\n• Represent clients in litigation involving a diverse range of legal fields, including land use, employment law,\nconstruction law, and business litigation.\n• Frequently engaged to speak at conferences and organizations on the effects of Generative Artificial\nIntelligence on the workplace.\nLitigation Attorney\nHermes, Netburn, O’Connor & Spearing, P.C. (now Clyde & Co.) | Boston, MA Aug. 2019 - Oct. 2020\n• Authored civil complaints, answers to complaints, discovery requests, motions, and legal memoranda for\nvarious matters, including civil rights violations, employment law, contracts, insurance coverage, and\nproducts liability.\n• Researched case law, statutes, and regulations for numerous jurisdictions to engage in motion practice and\nprovide legal advice to clients.\n• Conducted depositions with a tailored focus to obtain relevant information in furtherance of clients’ legal\nrights and interests.\nAssociate Attorney\nSmith & Brink, P.C. (now King, Tilden, McEttrick & Brink, P.C.) | Braintree, MA Jan. 2017 – Aug. 2019\n• Represented insurance companies in litigation against healthcare providers engaging in fraudulent medical\nand billing practices in violation of the Federal Racketeer Influence and Corrupt Organizations Act.\n• Investig