hool, Prior Charter School Board President\n-- 6 of 11 --\n\nLisa K. Halushka\nProfessor of Law Emeritus\n390 Wynstone Cir N, Oakland, MI 48363 · · (248) 770-6717; lkhalushka@gmail.com\nDear Hiring Committee,\nThroughout my career I have reflected on how fortunate I am to do things professionally that I\nfeel passionate about. My career as a lawyer focused on children’s interests, specifically child\nabuse and neglect and delinquency – advocating for children and their safety as well as\nhandling cases in the juvenile criminal justice system. I then found passion in education as a\ntenured law professor and assistant dean, teaching Criminal Procedure, Criminal Law and\nEvidence. Most recently I was a superintendent and principal (combined in the title of Head of\nSchool) at a charter school in Oxford, Michigan. I miss the classroom and look forward to\nbecoming an adjunct professor at your university.\nI believe that my unique education and experience provides fitting expertise for this position.\nAs a trial lawyer for many years my focus is on persuasion, collaboration, and resolution. I am\na very skilled student and professor of the law. I was a law school professor for 16 years, chair\nof the department for my subject area and the Assistant Dean of my campus. My experience as\na professor includes live classroom settings and online classroom delivery.\nI have an extraordinary ability to lead a classroom – inspiring my students to have an interest\nin the subject matter, and guiding students through scaffolded lessons and challenging\nassessments to gain mastery of the material. I enjoy research, especially in topics that are\nchallenging and timely. My resume includes a list of my published materials and presentation\ntopics. As an Assistant Dean I had to opportunity to engage with my students who were at\npersonal or academic risk. That experience improved my teaching it revealed more about the\nwhole student and my ability to measure how their life experiences