th various regulations, including ITAR, EAR, FAA, FCC, and OFAC.\n➢ Navigating complex regulatory frameworks and ensuring adherence to legal requirements.\n➢ Promoting ethical business practices and mitigating risks associated with non-compliance.\n➢ Global Instruction in Space Law: Design and deliver comprehensive coursework on Space Law Ethics\nfor Continuing Legal Education (CLE), targeting a global audience via live and video presentations.\nExperience\nUSAA, San Antonio, TX — Associate General Counsel, Payments, Fintech (2018 – 2024)\nI help entrepreneurs and innovators navigate payments, banking, and fintech law at USAA Bank. Reg E,\nCC, UCC-4 and 4(a), NACHA, and other regulations are my specialties. Through USAA Innovation Lab\nprojects, I want to use technology to improve the world by making outstanding products.\nCitibank, Tampa, FL — Vice President, Senior Counsel (2016-2018)\nDigital Transformation: Leading corporate treasury and trade solutions digital transformation.\nCompliance: Understanding blockchain, bitcoin, and AI legislation. Ability to integrate finance and\ntechnology to create new solutions for corporate needs.\n-- 1 of 10 --\n\n2 | P a g e\nSunTrust, Atlanta, GA — First Vice President, Senior Counsel (2014-2016)\nManage patents, trademarks, copyrights, and associated conflicts. Plan strategically to safeguard and\nleverage intellectual property. Negotiate vendor service agreements, software licensing, and outsourcing\ncontracts. Risk Management: Assess and mitigate IP and legal risks.\nWestern Union, Denver, CO — Vice President, Intl. Product Compliance Team (2013-2014)\nI created global compliance initiatives at Western Union. I managed teams to secure international\nmoney transfers and electronic payments in 200 countries. I guided firms through complex money\ntransmission and privacy requirements to protect their data and comply with BSA/AML best practices.\nEU Financial Directives, GDPR, BSA/AML, KYC, and OFAC are my specialties.\nEduca