 Space Era of Challenges, Sponsored by Rey Juan Carlos University, Madrid, Spain (May 2024).\nPaper & Presentation: “The Next Giant Leap: Fostering Sustainable Space Operations through Legal\nInnovation”, Strathclyde 6th Annual Postgraduate Law Conference, Law in Motion: Unravelling the\nImpact of Contemporary Legal Trends in Research, Glasgow, Scotland, 25th - 26th June 2024\nEd Koellner. "Navigating the New Frontier: Ethical, Societal, and Legal Challenges in the Space\nEconomy," AIAA 2024-4825. AIAA AVIATION FORUM AND ASCEND 2024. July 2024. eISBN978-1-62410-\n716-0\n-- 2 of 10 --\n\nI am writing to express my interest in the Professor position at your esteemed university. With an\nextensive background in law, technology, and space economy, combined with a robust academic\nand professional portfolio, I am enthusiastic about the opportunity to contribute to your esteemed\ninstitution.\nMy diverse educational journey has equipped me with a comprehensive understanding of various\nlegal and technological domains. I will begin a part time Ph.D. program in Intellectual Property Law\nfrom Masaryk University, and I have an LL.M. in Air and Space Law from the University of Mississippi\nSchool of Law, an MS in Global Technology and Development from Arizona State University, a JD\nfrom Marquette University, an MBA from Texas Christian University, and a BA in Biochemistry from\nWest Virginia University. These qualifications, along with my executive education in FinTech from\nHarvard University and Cryptocurrency & Blockchain from MIT, have solidified my expertise in the\nintersection of law, technology, and global development.\nMy most recent role was as Associate General Counsel at USAA, I assist business leaders and\ninnovators in navigating the complexities of payments, banking, and fintech law. My previous\npositions at Citibank, SunTrust, and Western Union have honed my skills in digital transformation,\ncompliance, and global product management. These experiences have 