s for potential regulatory and business compliance violations across\nkey areas such as anti-bribery and corruption, corporate fraud, and business ethics.\n● Manage ethics and compliance program for Airbus’ helicopters division in North America.\nU.S. ATTORNEY’S OFFICE FOR THE NORTHERN DISTRICT OF TEXAS, Dallas, Texas\nAssistant U.S. Attorney, Economic Crimes & Public Corruption, 3/2020 – 5/2024\n● Led high-profile and complex investigations and prosecutions of white-collar offenses,\nincluding tax crime, foreign government official corruption, securities and commodities fraud,\nbribery, money laundering, corporate embezzlement, and government program fraud, often in\nparallel with federal regulators, including the SEC and CFTC.\n● Successfully tried jury trials for multimillion-dollar fraud, money laundering, and tax crimes.\n● Jury trial achievements include securing the conviction of a senior executive for one of the\nlargest educational benefit frauds in the history of the U.S. Department of Veterans Affairs, and\nthe conviction of an organized crime leader for a multimillion-dollar fraud scheme.\n● Corporate crime matters include a foreign public official corruption investigation into a\nmultinational company, a forced labor investigation into a global medical equipment\nmanufacturer, and a sprawling investigation into a financial institution for systemic anti-money\nlaundering compliance failures involving hundreds of millions of dollars in transactions.\n● Corruption and financial fraud cases include a multimillion-dollar bribery investigation into\nbank directors, the prosecution of a business consultant for large-scale tax fraud, and the\nprosecution of non-profit and corporate officials for major bank fraud and embezzlement.\n● Securities \tand \tcommodities \tfraud \tmatters \tinclude \tinsider \ttrading \tinvestigations \tinto\nexecutives, the multimillion-dollar fraud prosecution of a cryptocurrency promoter, the\nprosecution of a forex trader, and a fraud investigation into a real estate development company.\nU.S. DEPARTMENT OF THE TREASURY, Washington, DC\nInvestigative Counsel, Special Inspector General for Pandemic Recovery, 7/2022 – 6/2023\n● On a detail from DOJ, advised Special Inspector General senior leadership on strategic\ninitiatives to identify, investigate, and prosecute fraudulent schemes affecting pandemic relief.\n● Coordinated nationwide investigations involving multibillion-dollar government programs.\n● Prosecuted the largest Pandemic Response Accountability Committee Fraud Task Force case.\nPILLSBURY WINTHROP SHAW PITTMAN LLP, Washington, DC\nCounsel, Corporate Investigations and White-Collar Defense, 10/2012 – 2/2020\n● Defended corporations and executives in high-stakes government investigations, litigation, and\nregulatory enforcement actions involving complex criminal and civil white-collar matters.\n● Successfully \tassisted \tclients \treach \tfavorable \tresolutions \tin \tinvestigations \tby \tfederal\nprosecutors and agencies, including the DOJ, SEC, IRS, FEC, OFAC, BIS, and OCC.\n-- 2 of 10 --\n\n2 of 2\n● Represented multiple foreign banks in groundbreaking DOJ Tax Division program providing\na path for Swiss financial institutions to resolve allegations of facilitating tax evasion.\n● Conducted internal investigations for companies operating throughout the U.S. and overseas\nand in various industries, including manufacturing, retail, tech, defense, and financial services.\n● Defended major U.S. corporations in sensitive civil and criminal government investigations\ninvolving allegations of economic sanctions evasion and export controls violations.\n● Defended former FIFA official in landmark DOJ corruption and fraud prosecution related to\nthe sale of TV and media rights in connection with FIFA’s World Cup soccer tournament.\n● Member of trial team defending executive in high-profile foreign corruption jury trial.\n● Represented prominent NCAA Division I men’s basketball in DOJ inv