didates and supervising\ninterns/externs\n Co-Chair of the Legal Technology Task Force\nCommunity Health Center of Southeast Kansas, Inc. Pittsburg, KS\nDeputy General Counsel, September 2021-April 2023\n Provided regulatory analysis, contract review and drafting, litigation support, and legal guidance for a\nFederally Qualified Health Center (FQHC) with 17 permanent locations in Kansas and Oklahoma.\n Drafted and reviewed proposed contractual arrangements with physicians, suppliers, and lessors\n Ensured compliance with multiple federal and state statutes and regulations\n Advised Chief Compliance Officer and General Counsel on legal matters, including new statutes and\nregulations, employment disputes, and litigation matters\n Provided regulatory analysis for committees including Safety, Morbidity & Mortality,\nOperations, Health Disparities Task Force, and Clinical Advancement\n As needed, facilitated credentialing of providers, including license applications, payor enrollments, and\nCHC/SEK privileging\n Managed legal interns within the organization, including intern selection and assignment of projects\nThomson Reuters Eagan, MN/Remote\nWestlaw Student Representative, August 2019-May 2021\n Educated students on Westlaw research interface, organized on-campus events including product\ndemonstrations, and addressed student technical issues with the Westlaw interface\n-- 2 of 11 --\n\nEDUCATION\nThe University of Alabama School of Law\nJuris Doctor, May 2021\n Articles Editor, The Journal of the Legal\nProfession, Vol. 45\n Chairperson, Career Services Office Board\n Treasurer, Bench and Bar Legal Honor Society\n Academic Scholarship\n GPA: 3.349\nTuscaloosa, AL\n CALI Excellence for the Future Award\n(Best Paper) — Transactional Drafting,\nFall 2020\n Secretary, Well-Balanced Society: A\nMental Health and Wellness Organization\n UA Law in Australia, Summer 2019\nMcNeese State University Lake Charles, LA\nBachelor of Science in Marketing, May 2018