81	109	nguyen_hung_5698127.pdf	\N	Dear Texas A&M recruiters:\nHi, I just wanted to introduce myself. My name is Hung “Huck” Nguyen I had been a lecturer at\nRMIT-Vietnam University for over 15 years. I really did enjoy working at RMIT-Vietnam but\nmoved back to the US in January, 2023, and currently enjoy teaching Civil Procedure, Real\nProperty and Contracts at Purdue Law School (online) as well as teaching at the University of\nHouston Law School as an Adjunct Professor.\nThere are a few things that I do really enjoy and excel at doing. One, I love interacting and\nteaching/training people. I enjoy being able to assist and mold eager minds to help them achieve\nwhat they thought was impossible. What tends to get missed a lot these days in education is the\nattention to detail to students and learners. A lot of institutions and even teachers tend to see\nstudents as numbers or targets that need to be met. Teachers need to build relationships and it is\nthose relationships that allow organizations to grow. Relationships with students and relationships\nwith other teachers’ is the backbone to any learning organization’s success. I excel at building and\nfostering relationships which has always been a strength of mine. Once you break through and\nconnect with students so much can be achieved. This ability has given me the opportunity to win\nthe top GTS scores at RMIT for numerous semesters as well as stellar scores at Purdue and UH.\nAdditionally, I love being challenged to do a wide range of things. In other words, diversity is the\nspice of life. I love developing different processes or projects and seeing it to fruition. I enjoy\nsetting challenging goals and meeting them. I love teaching a wide range of classes. At RMIT\nVietnam, I have luckily received the opportunity to teach a wide range of classes such as\nCommercial Law, Investment Law, Company Law, Business Communications, Corporate Social\nResponsibility, Intro to Management, Organizational Analysis, Leadership and Decision Making,\nEthics and Governance, and finally Work in Global Society. It was a highly rewarding experience.\nI believe that these positive and diverse experiences brought more success to both myself, as well\nas RMIT Vietnam.\nI am now really enjoying teaching law to mature students as the interaction and communication\nwith them has been tremendous. I believe I have excelled as a Professor of Law here at Purdue and\nUH based on the positive reviews of my teaching on the student surveys.\nWith that being said, I would like the opportunity to continue developing and building relationships\nas well as challenging myself to more diverse experiences by becoming an Adjunct Professor at\nyour university.\nThank you for your time and attention. I hope to get the opportunity to talk to you soon.\nWarmest regards,\nHuck Nguyen\nHung “Huck” Nguyen\n-- 1 of 10 --\n\nHung "Huck" Nguyen\n14035 Cashel Forest Dr., Houston, TX 77069\nHihuck@hotmail.com\n____________________________ 915-900-2828 ____________________________\nOBJECTIVE: Dynamic lecturer with demonstrated abilities in educating young minds,\npossessing strong communication and resolution skills, seeks a challenge in a unique and\nstimulating environment with room for personal and professional growth.\nEXPERIENCE:\n01/2024 - Date ADJUNCT/PROFESSOR OF LAW University of Houston\nHouston, TX\nDuties: Adjunct Professor of Law – Foreign LLM Program\nContracts I - Lecture on basic foundations of contract law, the legal body that encompasses both\nthe origination, enforcement and ultimate enactment of all legal contracts or agreements.\nCivil Procedure – Lecture on the foundation of civil procedure.\n01/2023 – Date PROFESSOR OF LAW Purdue Global/Concord LA, CA\nDuties: Online Adjunct Professor of Law\nReal Property I – Lecture on basic foundations of real property law covering many different\ntopics related to land ownership and the use of the land. It deals with title and ownership rights, as\nwell as the limitations on those rights.\nContracts I - Lecture on basic foundations of contract law, the legal body that encompasses both\nthe origination, enforcement and ultimate enactment of all legal contracts or agreements.\n08/2007 – 01/2023 LECTURER RMIT HCMC, Vietnam\nDuties: Course Coordinator and Lecturer for various courses.\nCommercial Law - Lecture on commercial law of Australia emphasizing the formulation and\ndrafting of contracts. Additionally, lecture on tort laws and specifically negligence.\nCorporations Law - Lecture on corporations’ law of Australia emphasizing the formulation of\nvarious types of corporations. Additionally, lecture on business enterprise with an emphasis on\nCorporate Governance and Regulations as well as Corporate Social Responsibility.\nWork in Global Society – Lecture and train students on the technology and the dynamic\nenvironment that is currently the industry. Discuss its application/ usage and how it can be\nutilized to further the growth of the industry.\n-- 2 of 10 --\n\nIntro To Management – Lecture on motivating employees, management theories, culture, global\nperspectives, managing change and innovation.\nOrganizational Behaviour - Lecture on behavior, perceptions, individual behaviours, decision\nmaking, creativity and team dynamics.\n09/2005 – 08/2007 PARTNER LuatViet HCMC, Vietnam\nDuties: Supervising attorney dealing with foreign clients, ranging from sole-proprietors to multi-\nnational companies, investing in Vietnam. Provide legal advice and assistance with any and all\naspects dealing with foreign investments from cradle-to-grave. Supervising attorney for such\nhigh-profile clients such as Coca-Cola, Nike CR Compliance, PSA (Port of Singapore Authority),\nMidea, Navigos Group, Dynapac, McCartney Communications and Bluescope Buildings.\n▪ Draft Licensing Agreements/ Support Agreement and assist with financial procurement\nof funds from the local bank for a UK media communications company.\n▪ Represent and advise foreign 