inistration with the unions. Additionally, I\nwas responsible for internal affairs investigations, discipline and worked as a liaison with the Town Human\nResources Department. I coordinated the recruitment, selection and background investigations for all new\nhires, sworn and non-sworn; and continued to assist employees with worker’s compensation, FMLA, and\nother employee needs throughout their employment.\nWhile a member of the Madison Police Department, my duties included serving as our Commission on\nAccreditation for Law Enforcement Agencies, Inc. (CALEA) Accreditation Manager, as well as the manager\nof our State of Connecticut Accreditation program, Training Officer, Public Information Officer, and\nInternal Affairs Investigator. I managed the department budget of approximately $4 million, oversaw our\ncommunications center and all civilian staff, and managed our recruitment efforts for all positions, sworn\nand non-sworn. I guided the Madison Police Department through a successful CALEA initial onsite\naccreditation in December 2013, and a successful State of Connecticut Accreditation in September 2014.\nAdditionally, we received CALEA Public Safety Accreditation in conjunction with our Law Enforcement\naccreditation in 2017, and have continued to be a multi-accredited agency throughout my time with the\ndepartment. An emphasis of my duties was compliance matters at the state and national levels.\nThroughout my time in Madison, I worked collaboratively with the other public safety service entities,\nincluding two fire departments and separate ambulance service, and fulfilled numerous roles in our\ncommunity’s ICS program including planning, logistics, operations, finance and public information officer.\nAs a community we used the ICS format for scheduled events such as our annual fireworks as well as our\nresponse to major weather events including severe thunderstorms, tropical storms and winter\nstorms/blizzards. I have completed the FEMA Independent Study