ding legal updates, strategy, pending matters and pre-litigation disputes. Provide strategic advice\nregarding business impact of existing or potential litigation and risk mitigation/management. Conduct\ndue diligence relating to potential acquisitions. Practice primarily focuses on commercial, employment,\ncompetition, consumer products, and intellectual property litigation, as well as complex, high-stakes\nclass actions. Extensive experience in trials, depositions, multi-district litigation, mediations, hearings,\nwitness preparation, document preservation, electronic discovery, appeals, expert witnesses, oral\narguments, and overall case management for complex matters with significant damages exposure.\nReview, draft, revise and negotiate company policies, internal guidelines, training and third-party\ncontracts. Routinely address international cross-over issues stemming from U.S. litigation relating to\noverseas \toperations. \tStrengths \tinclude \texceptional \tanalytical \tskills, oral \tadvocacy, \twritten\ncommunication, \tnegotiation \tstrategies, relationship retention, \tsound \tbusiness \tjudgment, \tteam\ndevelopment, \tgoal-orientation, \tstrategy \tdevelopment \tand \timplementation, \tprioritization, \trisk\nmitigation and collaboration.\n-- 1 of 9 --\n\nK IMBERLY F. RICH\n_____________________________________________________________________________________\nLEGAL EXPERIENCE, cont'd\nBoard of Trustees of Parish Episcopal School \tDallas, Texas\nMember of Board of Trustees (2012 to 2022); Member of Executive Committee and Chair of Risk\nManagement Committee (2014 to 2021); Member of Risk Management Committee (2010 to present)\nIdentify and mitigate risk for educational institution with multiple campuses; oversee major business,\nfinancial and operational risks to assure Board and management that risks are identified and properly\nmanaged; review and analyze committee charters, bylaws, policies and procedures; meet and confer\nwith auditors to conduct