gement process for the new\ncompany.\n• Successfully handled $85 million tax-related dispute and several government\ninvestigations.\n• Helped lead establishment of new corporate development function, identifying and\ninvestigating potential acquisitions and managing purchase process.\n• Closed $800M acquisition and associated debt funding.\nMWH Global, Inc. May 2012 to June 2013\nBroomfield, Colorado\nMWH Global, Inc. (now part of Stantec Inc.) was an engineering, construction services and\nmanagement consulting company that was ranked as a world leader in water. The firm,\nheadquartered in a suburb of Denver, had annual revenues of approximately $1.6 billion and\n8000 employees in 180 offices located in 31 countries.\nChief Legal and Risk Officer; Corporate Secretary\n• Managed a department of 41, with responsibility for legal, contractual and insurance\nmatters. Also responsible for employee ethics and compliance training and\ninvestigations.\n-- 2 of 11 --\n\nMARK D. SCHULTZ\nPage 3 of 6\n• Helped to prepare the company for possible public offering, including “public\ncompany” corporate governance procedures, claims reporting and reserve process,\nand Audit Committee reporting.\n• Reviewed and helped to revise company capital structure, revolving credit line, and\nprocesses for SEC registration exemption obligations and securities reporting\nrequirements in applicable foreign jurisdictions.\n• Closed acquisition of Australian environmental consulting company.\n• Established new company processes in government gratuities, foreign sales agent\nengagements, and outside counsel cost management and budgeting.\nSRA International, Inc. June 2008 to August 2011\nFairfax, Virginia\nSRA International, Inc. (after a recent merger, part of General Dynamics) was a\ntechnology, information and health services company. The Company was traded on the\nNew York Stock Exchange and generated $1.8 billion in annual revenues through more\nthan 7,300 employees and offices in 30 states