ing effectively communicating with all levels of the organization, presenting complex information\nclearly, assessing and mitigating risk with practical strategies that advance business objectives, and responding\nthoughtfully rather than reacting to difficult situations.\nThe most impactful class I took in law school was a negotiation class taught by two adjunct professors. The\npractical takeaways from that class have been invaluable in my daily practice. I would appreciate the\nopportunity to pay that forward by teaching your students about health law, regulatory compliance, data\nprivacy, AI, incident response, negotiation and other soft skills, or other adjacent topics as needs arise.\nThank you for considering my application. I look forward to the opportunity to discuss how my experience and\nskills can benefit your program.\nWarm regards,\nJENNIFER TAVERAS, JD, CHC, CIPP/C/US\n-- 1 of 11 --\n\nJ ENNIFER W. TAVERAS, JD, CHC, CIPP/US/C\n7795 BARBER RANCH RD  FORT W ORTH, TX 76126  832-454-6644  WJTAVERAS@ATT.NET\nEXPERIENCE\nAlcon Inc., Fort Worth, TX \tJune 2023 – Present\nRegional Privacy Officer – US & Canada\n• \tResponsible for leading the US and Canadian Privacy Program and strategy for all franchises.\n• \tReviews, develops and advises on privacy policies, notices, consent language and functionality, training and\ncommunications.\n• \tLeads privacy investigations, risk assessments and incident response.\n• \tSupports privacy by design in medical devices, software, websites, applications, projects and initiatives through\nprivacy assessments, data mapping and ongoing advice and counsel.\n• \tLeads privacy due diligence, contracting and integration for M&A activities.\n• \tProvides legal support to Product and IT Security teams.\n• \tNegotiates privacy and data protection terms in commercial agreements.\n• \tPartners with other legal, compliance and business stakeholders on privacy-related matters.\n• \tServes on North America Compliance Committee, Resp