 addition, I have experience with continuing education\nprograms as a course facilitator at eCornell, the distance education provider of Cornell University. Lastly, I have the\ndistinct privilege of serving with Dr. Nathan Harness in the Texas A&M University Financial Planning program\nwhere I created and teach the online Estate Planning course for undergraduates. My experience teaching and\ncreating courses in an online JD program and other distance education experience is perfectly complementary to\nteaching in the distance education programs of Texas A&M University School of Law.\nThird, I am engaged in active service at Texas A&M University and in the legal profession. I serve as a class agent\nfor the Fightin’ Texas Aggie class of 2007 and serve as a mentor in the Rister ’74 Agribusiness Entrepreneurship\nProgram at Texas A&M University. Professionally, I am engaged with the International, Tax, and Real Estate,\nProbate, and Trust Law sections of the State Bar of Texas. I am a featured speaker at several professional events\nthroughout the year.\nI look forward to the opportunity to serve the distance education students of Texas A&M University School of\nLaw. For further information, see my resume. You may contact me at the address listed above, my email address,\nor at (972) 310-9541.\nSincerely,\nSam C. Webb\n-- 1 of 9 --\n\nSAMUEL C. WEBB\n19511 Cloverstone Court 972.310.9541\nHouston, Texas 77094 swebb@tamu.edu\nPROFESSIONAL EXPERIENCE\nThe Webb Law Firm, PLLC, d/b/a Webb Strahan, PLLC – Houston, TX\nPartner – January 2022 – Present\n▪ Litigate ad valorem tax lawsuits in Texas and advise clients on application of property tax law\n▪ Counsel clients on compliance with state and federal tax, wealth management, and economic regulations\n▪ Perform general counsel services, including strategic advice, legal counsel, and compliance\nFreedom Day Solutions, LLC – Houston, TX\nWealth Advisor – January 2023 – Present\n▪ Advise clients on portfolio investment manageme