r undergraduates as part of new Financial Planning major\n▪ Engage in online teaching of Estate Planning course by teaching, grading, and managing the course\n▪ Serve with faculty and director to recruit students, develop program goals, and advocate for the program\nTrinity Law School – Santa Ana, CA\nAdjunct Professor, August 2021 – Present\n▪ Teach several core and elective law school courses through the Canvas LMS\n▪ Develop and teach new online course – Negotiation in Law and Business – and serve as Subject Matter Expert\n▪ Develop and teach new online course – Survey of Federal Taxation – and serve as Subject Matter Expert\nHouston Christian University – Houston, TX\nAdjunct Professor – October 2019 – Present\n▪ Teach Business Ethics (UG) through Blackboard and Legal Environment of Business (UG) on campus\n-- 2 of 9 --\n\n*References Available Upon Request\n▪ Develop new online course – The American Courts – and serve as Subject Matter Expert\nCornell University – Ithaca, NY\nCourse Facilitator – eCornell – May 2022 – December 2023\n▪ Served as course facilitator for the Business and Legal Studies program with eCornell on Canvas LMS\n▪ Courses facilitated:\no LAW531 – Foundations of Ethical Reasoning\no LAW534 – Addressing Dysfunctional Ethical Cultures\no LSM571 – Introduction to Negotiation\no LSM572 – Integrative Negotiation\nTexas A&M University-Central Texas – Killeen, TX\nAdjunct Professor – College of Business Administration, August 2015 – August 2020, August 2022 – December 2022\n▪ Taught Legal Environment of Business (UG) & International Business Law (G) through Blackboard\n▪ Administered, graded, and provided feedback on exams, assignments, and course papers\nEDUCATION\nTexas Tech University School of Law – Lubbock, TX\nDoctor of Jurisprudence – Business Law Certificate – May 2010\n▪ 2009 NLLSA National Moot Court Champion – Best Petitioner’s Brief and Top Oralist\n▪ 2009 American Association for Justice National Mock Trial Team – Lead Chair\nReformed